# game/dlgs/mortuary_zombies/zm257.rpy:57
translate english zm257_s2_e5a12faa:

    # 'zm257_s2{#zm257_s2}'
    nr 'The spirit blasts back into the body with such violence that, with a single great muscular contraction, the corpse is hurtled backwards!{#zm257_s2_1}'
    nr 'The body is on its feet again in an instant, dancing and thrashing about madly, waving its arms and popping its stitches, flaps of loosened flesh flopping about as it prances to and fro, eyes goggling and rolling about in its head, giggling madly all the while…{#zm257_s2_1}'

# game/dlgs/mortuary_zombies/zm257.rpy:72
translate english zm257_s3_e2a46bcb:

    # 'zm257_s3{#zm257_s3}'
    nr 'The possessed corpse sings as it leaps and whirls about, the volume and pitch of its voice rising and falling in random patterns.{#zm257_s3_1}'
    zm257 '«YOU are the SPIRIT I, the LIVING, answer my questions YOU SHALL!»{#zm257_s3_2}'
    nr 'Your confused expression seems to please it; it hooks its bony fingers into its mouth and pulls it into a ghastly grin, laughing maniacally and waggling its pasty, white tongue.{#zm257_s3_3}'

# game/dlgs/mortuary_zombies/zm257.rpy:93
translate english zm257_s4_2a2dee63:

    # 'zm257_s4{#zm257_s4}'
    nr 'The spirit seems to become calm for a moment before exploding into a stream of mind-numbingly loud, babbled nonsense. The cacophony is almost maddening; it threatens to drive you to your knees. And as abruptly as it began… it stops. The corpse stands there, twitching quietly.{#zm257_s4_1}'

# game/dlgs/mortuary_zombies/zm257.rpy:113
translate english zm257_s5_c4bab705:

    # 'zm257_s5{#zm257_s5}'
    nr 'Again the spirit sings.{#zm257_s5_1}'
    zm257 '«Questions OF THE living shall the DEAD answer THE; SO it was, is IT so, shall so IT BE. You my ANSWER will questions!»{#zm257_s5_2}'
    nr 'The look on your face seems to please it wildly; it begins to cavort so madly that you wonder if the corpse can take the abuse.{#zm257_s5_3}'
    nr 'You can almost hear its bones creak and fracture, tendons snapping, as it spins and hurls itself about.{#zm257_s5_3}'

# game/dlgs/mortuary_zombies/zm257.rpy:134
translate english zm257_s6_f607ca91:

    # 'zm257_s6{#zm257_s6}'
    nr 'As the spirit fades away from the corpse, its jabbering mouth twists into a knowing smile.{#zm257_s6_1}'
    nr 'Its wild, flashing eyes bore into you with the piercing glare of a psychopath, and it whispers a single, carefully-formed word, drawn out like a string of precious pearls.{#zm257_s6_1}'
    zm257 '«Limbo…»{#zm257_s6_2}'

# game/dlgs/mortuary_zombies/zm257.rpy:150
